---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base
  title="mk-qa-master · AI 測試大師 — let's make QA simple"
  description="MCP server that drives web (pytest / Jest / Cypress / Go) and mobile (Maestro on iOS + Android, incl. BlueStacks) test suites. Analyze, generate, run, advise — every run."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <img src="/assets/logo.png" alt="mk-qa-master" class="hero-logo" />
      <span class="eyebrow">Member 1 · Execution side of the loop</span>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Let's make <span class="accent">QA</span> simple.</h1>
      <p class="hero-alt-name">AI 測試大師 · MK QA MASTER</p>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        mk-qa-master is an MCP server that drives <strong>web</strong>
        (pytest / Jest / Cypress / Go) and <strong>mobile</strong>
        (Maestro on iOS + Android, incl. BlueStacks) test suites —
        writes the next round from a URL or a live screen, and acts as
        your data-driven QA advisor every single run.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/kao273183/mk-qa-master">GitHub →</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://pypi.org/project/mk-qa-master/">PyPI</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/kao273183/mk-qa-master/blob/main/README.md">Read the docs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">What it does</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Three jobs. <span class="accent">One server.</span></h2>
        <p class="section-sub">Web + mobile, ranked by how often you actually use them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="icon">▶</div>
          <h3>Run tests · web or mobile</h3>
          <p>Switch runners with a single <code>QA_RUNNER</code> env var: <strong>pytest / Jest / Cypress / Go</strong> for web, <code>maestro</code> for iOS Simulator, Android Emulator, real devices, BlueStacks. Auto-retry, JUnit XML, screenshots, Playwright trace.zip — out of the box.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="icon">✎</div>
          <h3>Write tests from a URL or a screen</h3>
          <p><code>analyze_url</code> probes the DOM; <code>analyze_screen</code> dumps the live mobile hierarchy. Both surface form / cta / nav / tab-bar modules with real selectors; <code>generate_test</code> emits runnable pytest <em>or</em> Maestro YAML — not <code># TODO</code> placeholders.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="icon">⚡</div>
          <h3>Your QA optimization advisor</h3>
          <p>Every run archives a snapshot and writes a new <code>optimization-plan.md</code>. Flaky vs. broken vs. slow-regression — ranked by evidence, not by gut. Same loop works for web and mobile.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block" style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">Status</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">v0.5.1 · <span class="accent">16 tools</span> · 5 runners</h2>
        <p class="section-sub">
          Full tool surface, install instructions, prompting cookbook,
          and architecture notes live in the README.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align: center;">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/kao273183/mk-qa-master#readme">Read the full README →</a>
        &nbsp;
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/spec-master">Sibling: mk-spec-master →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
